# Step 9: Field Creation and Object Configuration

In this step, fields are created for the custom objects and the standard **Case** object used in the **AI-Powered Customer Support Ticketing System**.

The following objects are configured:

1. AI Feedback (Custom Object)
2. Support Category (Custom Object)
3. SLA Policy (Custom Object)
4. Case (Standard Object)

---

# 1. AI Feedback (AI_Feedback__c) – Custom Object

This object stores feedback provided by support agents on AI-generated suggestions.

| Field Label        | API Name              | Data Type                                                            | Purpose                     |
| ------------------ | --------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------- |
| AI Feedback Number | Name                  | Auto Number                                                          | Unique feedback record      |
| Case               | Case__c               | Lookup (Case)                                                        | Related support case        |
| Feedback Status    | Feedback_Status__c    | Picklist (Helpful, Not Helpful)                                      | Agent rating of AI output   |
| AI Suggestion Type | AI_Suggestion_Type__c | Picklist (Case Classification, Priority Prediction, Suggested Reply) | Type of AI suggestion       |
| Agent Comments     | Agent_Comments__c     | Long Text Area                                                       | Agent remarks on AI quality |
| Created By         | CreatedById           | Lookup (User)                                                        | Agent who provided feedback |
| Created Date       | CreatedDate           | Date/Time                                                            | Feedback timestamp          |

---

# 2. Support Category (Support_Category__c) – Custom Object

This object stores different categories of customer support issues.

| Field Label           | API Name            | Data Type | Purpose                     |
| --------------------- | ------------------- | --------- | --------------------------- |
| Support Category Name | Name                | Text      | Issue category name         |
| Description           | Description__c      | Text Area | Category description        |
| Default Priority      | Default_Priority__c | Picklist  | Default priority suggestion |
| Active                | Active__c           | Checkbox  | Category availability       |

---

# 3. SLA Policy (SLA_Policy__c) – Custom Object

This object defines SLA rules for resolving cases based on priority.

| Field Label             | API Name               | Data Type                    | Purpose                 |
| ----------------------- | ---------------------- | ---------------------------- | ----------------------- |
| SLA Policy Name         | Name                   | Text                         | SLA policy identifier   |
| Priority Level          | Priority_Level__c      | Picklist (High, Medium, Low) | Case priority           |
| Resolution Time (Hours) | Resolution_Time__c     | Number                       | Allowed resolution time |
| Escalation Required     | Escalation_Required__c | Checkbox                     | Escalation flag         |

---

# 4. Case – Standard Object

The **Case object** is used to track and manage customer support requests.

| Field Label           | API Name                 | Data Type           | Purpose                               |
| --------------------- | ------------------------ | ------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| Case Number           | CaseNumber               | Auto Number         | Unique case identifier                |
| Subject               | Subject                  | Text                | Case title                            |
| Description           | Description              | Long Text Area      | Customer issue text analyzed by AI    |
| Status                | Status                   | Picklist            | Case lifecycle status                 |
| Priority              | Priority                 | Picklist            | Case urgency (AI predicted or manual) |
| Issue Type            | Issue_Type__c            | Picklist            | AI classified issue category          |
| SLA Due Date          | SLA_Due_Date__c          | Date/Time           | SLA deadline                          |
| AI Suggested Response | AI_Suggested_Response__c | Long Text Area      | AI recommended reply                  |
| Owner                 | OwnerId                  | Lookup (User/Queue) | Assigned support agent                |

---

# Result

After completing this step:

• Custom objects store AI insights and SLA configurations
• Case records track customer issues
• AI suggestions and feedback are stored for analysis
• SLA policies define response timelines

These fields enable automation, reporting, and AI-assisted support within the **Salesforce Customer Support Ticketing System**.
